<methods><methodStep><description><section><title>Butterfly Survey</title>
<para>Recorded butterfly species seen within transects as distance away from a habitat edge increased. Distance varied depending on the size of the habitat itself. Transects were 50 meters long by 10 meters wide and ran parallel to the habitat edge. Data was collected by meandering within each transect for 20 minutes, recording all butterflies seen within the transect. Temperature, light levels and shrub density were also recorded.Each plot was surveyed twice throughoutt the course of the summer, with each plot having three transects. The order in which transects and plots were surveyed was randomized. All collections occured between 11 am and 4 pm.</para>
</section>
</description>
<instrumentation>Kestrel 2000 pocket wind meter</instrumentation>
